# Svelte 5 — patterns and restrictions

## Runes — mandatory

```svelte
<script lang="ts">
  // ✅ Svelte 5 runes
  let count = $state(0)
  const double = $derived(count * 2)
  const { title, items = [] }: Props = $props()

  // ❌ Do NOT use Svelte 4 store syntax
  // import { writable } from 'svelte/store'
</script>
```

## Page data

```svelte
<script lang="ts">
  import { page } from '$app/state'
  import type { PageData } from '../../routes/some/$types'

  // Data from page.data, not from $props()
  const data: PageData = page.data as PageData
</script>
```

## {@const} — only inside block tags

```svelte
<!-- ✅ Correct — as the first child of {#each} -->
{#each items as item (item.id)}
  {@const meta = getMediaTypeMeta(item.mediaType)}
  <div class={meta.color}>...</div>
{/each}

<!-- ❌ Wrong — inside an HTML element -->
<div>
  {@const meta = ...}  <!-- Svelte error -->
</div>
```

## Dynamic CSS classes — use inline style

Tailwind JIT does not include dynamically concatenated class names. Use `style=` for colours from variables.

```svelte
<!-- ❌ Purge will drop bg-green-500 when built from a variable -->
<div class="rounded-full {statusMeta.color}">

<!-- ✅ Inline style -->
<div class="rounded-full" style="background-color: {statusMeta.bgColor}">
```

## Lucide icons

Use current names (not deprecated ones):

```svelte
<!-- ✅ -->
import CircleCheckIcon from '@lucide/svelte/icons/circle-check'
import CirclePlayIcon from '@lucide/svelte/icons/circle-play'

<!-- ❌ deprecated, no .svelte.d.ts -->
import CheckCircleIcon from '@lucide/svelte/icons/check-circle'
import PlayCircleIcon from '@lucide/svelte/icons/play-circle'
```

## Navigation

```svelte
import { onNavigate, beforeNavigate, afterNavigate } from '$app/navigation'
```

Page transitions via the View Transitions API are already configured in `layout.svelte`.

## HTML sanitisation

Descriptions from external APIs may contain HTML. Always sanitise before rendering:

```svelte
import { sanitizeHtml, stripHtml } from '$shared/lib/html'

<!-- For full description rendering -->
{@html sanitizeHtml(media.overview)}

<!-- For card previews (short text) -->
{stripHtml(media.overview)}
```
